 The results of a Yougov survey carried out last year found that men are most likely to want to receive a card, chocolate or a nice dinner out, with some also saying alcohol and jewellery are gifts they would be happy to be given. Showing a partner you've thought of something personally to give them is going to mean a lot when they open it on Valentine's Day. Personalised gifts are a good way to give a keepsake that will be kept for a long time, while an experience like a meal out is a good way to spend time together. MORE LIKE THIS